  "texts": [
    "But let us mention that, by simply restricting to the class of H-type nilpotent Lie groups [Kap80,Kap81] -which are known to admit nilsoliton metrics [Lau01]-one already gets a very rich class of examples.",
    "Indeed, from the explicit description of G that may be found in [Saa96] (albeit without the unimodularity constraint), it follows that the symmetric spaces arising from H-type nilpotent Lie groups contain irreducible factors from 8 out of the 10 infinite families in the classification (the missing ones are SL n (C)/SU(n) and SU(p, q)/S(U(p) × U(q))).Regarding other non-gradient Ricci solitons, up to very recently, the homogeneous ones were the only source of examples.",
    "First constructed by Lauret in [Lau01] (see also [BD07,Lot07]), they have been quite extensively studied in the last 20 years, see [Lau09,Jab15,BL23a] and the references therein.",
    "Beyond the homogeneous case, some non-gradient expanders asymptotic to Euclidean cones were obtained in [KL12].",
    "More recently, examples on surfaces were constructed in [TY24]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}